	   <tr><td colspan=2>Idealy you want a weapon that is less than 2 stones.&nbsp;&nbsp;As well as one that does better damage than your fist.  <br><br>Also you shouldn't be too concerned about keeping all of your skills maxed.  I have personally learned new weapon skills well into the 40's, and I know people who have lerned them lvl 50+.  However if possible it is always best to rase all of your skills.  <br><br>If you search the weapons tables you will notice a few things:<br>Most of the good hand to hand weapons drop on Luclin.<br>Most of the light blunt weapons can not be aquired at lower lvls and sell for considerable sum to a new player.  <br><br>There is one new exception to this.  The Club of Gnoll Bashing 7/28 and about 2 stones.  This Club is the result of a quest given out by the new lady near the fire near the SFG zone in QH.  This weapon will out damage your fist until lvl 29 or so.<br><br>Another choice would be to travel to the Cat starting zone.  In the srounding zones is where the Horn type weapons drop.  You should be able to solo some of these mobs at your lvl.  However it would be very difficult for you to make the jurney.  <br><br>You can always travil to SH (tp in GF or NK) and search the merchants for Ulak's or Katar sold to merchants by players.  The PS Ulak is a rare find but sells for about 1.5pp from a merchant this weapon will out damage your hands until about lvl 39. The Heavy Iron Ulak is much cheeper and will be better than your hands until about lvl 20.<br><br>The Bogling Mallet can also be found at merchants for about 14pp it is 0.0 stones and will out damage your fist until about lvl 30.  It is a good weapon for gaininng skill and can be toted around with no weight concerns.  <br><br>Hand to hand is the most important weapon skill for young monks.  At higher lvls good 1hb are more common (lvl 40+) and thus this skill becomse more important as you lvl up.<br><br>Work on maxing your Hand to hand skill before worring about other weapons skills.<br><br>To learn a new weapon skill put at least 10 practices points into that weapon skill. Also remember that your ofence skill along with your weapons skill determains how often you hit and how much damage you do, so at worst your abilities will be about half of your lvl maxed skills.  Then use the new weapon in the primary hand when the amount of damage you do is not crtical to the success of the group. (Most groups have far more fire power than they need for the mobs they are killing) If your damage is more important then put the new weapon in your off hand.  And if needed you can alway put the weapon in invantory and use your lvl maxed hand to hand when your damage is important to the group.  <br><br>So do the quest (note if you are in Freeport you can travil to GF tp to the nexus and tp to Antinoc.  When facing the guard tower head to your right, along the water.  follow the water to the zone and throug the next zone until you hit the zone wall follow the zone wall until you reach the path or canyon.  The path will lead you to Qeyons.   This trip should be very safe for a person of your lvl.<br><br>A few more tips for the low lvl untwinked monk.<br><br>PW armor can be made at very low tailoring skill, the runied pelts are easy to obtain, and a number of them are less than 1 stone in weight.  I used PW to fill in most of the armor slots not coverd by the newbee quest armor. With a bit more skill in tailoring you can make raw silk armor, same ac as PW but all items are less than one stone.  Studded leather is the next easiest to make and have very good ac (for untwinked monks) and many of the items are less than one stone.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
